Parliament, Tuesday, 19 November 2019 – Tomorrow, on Wednesday 20 November at 15.00, Members of the National Assembly will ask oral questions to the Ministers from the Social Services Cluster. This cluster comprises of Minister of Higher Education, Science and Technology, the Minister of Basic Education, Minister of Human Settlement, Water and Sanitation, the Minister of Health and the Minister of Social Development..
	
	Parliament uses a range of instruments to hold the executive accountable as section 92(2) of the Constitution stipulates that Cabinet Members are accountable collectively and individually to Parliament for the exercise of their powers and performances of their functions.
	
	Among questions to be answered by the Minister of Higher Education, Science and Technology scheduled for tomorrow's plenary sitting are: For the full list of questions, please click on the following hyperlink:
	https://www.parliament.gov.za/storage/app/media/Docs/quest_pap/5c48860f-5882-4260-b0f3-a51ef5e1df6b.pdf The National Assembly plenary will tomorrow also consider the Report of the Standing Committee on Finance on the Division of Revenue Amendment Bill. This will be followed by a debate on the same Bill. Journalists and photographers who do not have Parliamentary media access permits and wish to cover the Sittings of the National Assembly should send their details (full name, ID/Passport number and name of the media house) to Mlindi Mpindi on 081 716 7329 or 021 403 2340 ormmpindi@parliament.gov.za ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENT OF THE REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICAEnquiries: Moloto Mothapo – 082 370 6930 Democracy is not an event that occurred in 1994. It is a process to which all of us can contribute by making our voices heard in Parliament, in the provincial legislatures and in broader society.Read more